Siege.'' Includes ``Glory,'' ``Malcolm X,'' ``Courage Under Fire,''
``Crimson Tide,'' ``He Got Game.'' (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-RINGEL _ For Shakespeare's birthday, a rundown of some
less obvious Bard works on film, including the 1930s version of ``A
Midsummer Night's Dream'' and the Richard Burton-Elizabeth Taylor
version of ``Taming of the Shrew.'' (Ringel, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 23
</P>
