<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Spotlight on. . . .
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Denzel Washington (``The Siege'')
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Glory'' (1989). Winning the supporting actor Oscar for this
Civil War drama (filmed partially in Georgia) about America's first
unit of black soldiers.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Malcolm X'' (1992). Earning an Oscar nomination for his
portrait of the slain leader in Spike Lee's epic biopic.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Courage Under Fire'' (1996). Investigating the in-battle
death of soldier Meg Ryan in this complex, engaging Gulf War drama.
That's Matt Damon in a small supporting role.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Crimson Tide'' (1995). Going head-to-head against commanding
officer Gene Hackman in this nukes-on-a-sub thriller.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``He Got Game'' (1998). Trying to break through to his
basketball-star son, on a tight deadline, in Spike Lee's drama.
</P>
<P>
   _ Steve Murray writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
