   COURT-DISABLED (Washington) _ Hearing arguments in a case that
could produce the decade's most important ruling on treatment for
mentally disabled people, several Supreme Court justices express
reservations about broadening a federal anti-bias law. Doing so,
they say, could force cash-strapped states to push people with
mental disabilities out on the streets. By MARK HELM.
</P>
