</P>
<P>
   VERSAILLES-CONSERVE (Chicago) _ Catherine Hamilton, president of
the American Friends of Versailles, has spent the past 18 months
losing sleep. The reason for her insomnia is Le Bal de Versailles,
a six-day extravaganza of Sun King proportions she is organizing in
France to raise $4.5 million to restore the Bosquet de Trois
Fontaines, the now-derelict garden masterpiece at the palace. By
Patricia Lee Brown.
