<HEADER>
A7500 &Cx1f; tad-z
r d &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FOOD-RECIPESWAP22-COX     04-21 0393
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FOOD-RECIPESWAP22-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Salad gets extra crunch with uncooked ramen noodles
 &HT;    By Marcia Lanhenry
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ When Linda Juckett said she wanted to make a tossed
salad that used uncooked ramen noodles, we learned there are lots
of variations on a potluck-popular theme.
</P>
<P>
   Susan Bennett e-mailed this one, given to her by Melanie Clem of
Marietta (Ga.). Though the noodles are not cooked in the usual way
_ boiled _ they are browned along with walnuts to add depth to the
salad's crunch.
</P>
<P>
   SALAD
</P>
<P>
   Crunchy Romaine Toss
</P>
<P>
   Makes 8 servings
</P>
<P>
   Preparation time: 15 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Cooking time: 5 minutes
</P>
<P>
   For the salad:
</P>
<P>
   4 tablespoons ( 1/2 stick) unsalted butter
</P>
<P>
   1 cup chopped walnuts
</P>
<P>
   1 (6-ounce) package Ramen noodles, uncooked, broken up
</P>
<P>
   1 bunch broccoli, coarsely chopped
</P>
<P>
   1 head romaine, washed,
</P>
<P>
   torn in pieces
</P>
<P>
   4 green onions, chopped
</P>
<P>
   For the dressing:
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup granulated sugar (or more to taste)
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup wine vinegar
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons soy sauce
</P>
<P>
   1 cup vegetable oil
</P>
<P>
   Salt and pepper to taste
</P>
<P>
   In a small skillet or saucepan, melt butter. Add walnuts and
noodles. Cook and stir until browned, 3 to 5 minutes. Cool on paper
towels. In a large bowl, combine broccoli, romaine and onions. Add
walnuts, noodles and dressing; toss.
</P>
<P>
   To make the dressing: In a medium bowl, combine sugar, vinegar
and soy sauce. Slowly whisk in oil. Season to taste with salt and
pepper.
</P>
<P>
   Per serving: 519 calories, 8 grams protein, 40 grams fat
(percent calories from fat, 70), 35 grams carbohydrates, 10
milligrams cholesterol, 790 milligrams sodium, 4 grams fiber.
</P>
<P>
   Recipe request
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Kay Ramers e-mails a request for a white cheese dip such as
that served in some Tex-Mex restaurants.
</P>
<P>
   Where to write
</P>
<P>
   Send food news to Food Department, The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution, P.O. Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302. The
deadline is noon two Mondays before publication.
</P>
<P>
   Editor: Susan Puckett at spuckett(at)ajc.com. 404-526-5443.
</P>
<P>
   Assistant editor: Marcia Langhenry at mlanghenry(at)ajc.com.
404-526-5418.
</P>
<P>
   Food and nutrition writer: Reagan Walker at rwalker(at)ajc.com.
</P>
<P>
   404-526-5856.
</P>
<P>
   Food writer/dining critic: John Kessler at jkessler(at)ajc.com.
404-526-5452.
</P>
