<HEADER>
A7509 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r d &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-RECIPES-BUNDY-TEX     04-21 0444
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RECIPES-BUNDY-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DIVE INTO THIS SHRIMP DIP FROM S.&AMP;D. OYSTER CO.
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BEVERLY BUNDY 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   A reader e-mails looking for the coleslaw recipe for Dallas'
S.&AMP;D. Oyster Co.
</P>
<P>
   The legendary restaurant is mum on that recipe but does share
the recipe for one of its popular appetizers.
</P>
<P>
   S.&AMP;D. OYSTER CO. SPICY SHRIMP DIP
</P>
<P>
   Yields 6 cups
</P>
<P>
   2 pounds peeled, deveined shrimp
</P>
<P>
   8-ounce package cream cheese, softened
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup mayonnaise
</P>
<P>
   1 cup Thousand Island dressing
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup minced scallions
</P>
<P>
   1 small onion, grated
</P>
<P>
   4 teaspoons Tabasco sauce
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon Lawry's seasoned salt
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon freshly ground horseradish
</P>
<P>
   Boil shrimp; chop.
</P>
<P>
   Blend cream cheese with mayonnaise and salad dressing.
</P>
<P>
   Stir in shrimp, minced scallions, grated onion, Tabasco sauce,
seasoned salt and horseradish.
</P>
<P>
   Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per tablespoon: 37 calories, 3 grams fat, 1
gram carbohydrates, 2 grams protein, 18 milligrams cholesterol, 78
milligrams sodium, 69 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Peggy Romine of Fort Worth writes looking for a recipe for
homemade ranch dressing. Here's one from ``The Complete Book of
Dressings'' by Paulette Mitchell (MacMillan, $12).
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   RANCH DRESSING
</P>
<P>
   Yields 1/2 cup
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup low-fat cottage cheese
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup low-fat buttermilk
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon freshly squeezed lemon juice
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon minced shallot
</P>
<P>
   1/4 teaspoon Dijon mustard
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon minced fresh oregano (or 1/4 teaspoon dried oregano)
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon minced fresh thyme leaves (or 1/4 teaspoon dried
thyme)
</P>
<P>
   1/8 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper, or to taste
</P>
<P>
   Dash salt, or to taste
</P>
<P>
   Place first 5 ingredients in a blender; puree until smooth. Stir
in remaining ingredients. Taste; adjust seasonings. Stir before
serving.
</P>
<P>
   To prepare in advance: If dried herbs are used, allow dressing
to stand for 15-30 minutes before serving. This dressing will keep
for 2 days in a tightly closed container in refrigerator.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per tablespoon: 8 calories, trace fat, 1
gram carbohydrates, 1 gram protein, trace cholesterol, 51
milligrams sodium, 14 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   (Beverly Bundy is food editor for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Send recipes and requests to Beverly Bundy, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, Box 1870, Fort Worth, Texas 76101. Or E-mail to
bbundy(at)star-telegram.com. Include a daytime phone number.
Responses to requests will be made only through this column. Visit
the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
