Davies, an actress famous as the paramour of the newspaper magnate
William Randolph Hearst. Before that it was known as the place
where Clark Gable and Carole Lombard stayed on their honeymoon. But
perhaps the best reason to know the Willows is that it was bought
shortly after it was built in 1927 by Samuel Untermeyer, a New York
civil rights lawyer and passionate horticulturist. By Jim Robbins.
