calls public housing a ``success story.'' He cites surveys showing
that 87 percent of the authorities running such facilities are in
good or excellent condition and that 75 percent of residents are
satisfied. But the surveys are drawn from mostly small- and
medium-sized cities, and do not include New York, Chicago, Los
