<HEADLINE>
A COMPARISON OF KIDS SITES 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NICKELODEON ONLINE: www.nick.com, www.nickjr.com and others.
</P>
<P>
   _ Number of unique visitors in February: 1.47 million.
</P>
<P>
   _ Number of visitors ages 2 to 11: 337,000.
</P>
<P>
   _ Content: Information on Nickelodeon TV shows, interactive
games, pre-school content and a parents' forum.
</P>
<P>
   _ Privacy policy: Does not collect personal information from
visitors.
</P>
<P>
   _ Advertising policy: On www.nickjr.com, ads appear only in
parent-directed areas, not in areas aimed at children. If a user
clicks on one that leads to an advertiser's Web site, a ``bumper
page'' appears. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DISNEY ONLINE: www.disney.com, www.family.com and Disney foreign
language sites.
</P>
<P>
   _ Number of unique visitors in February: 4.6 million.
</P>
<P>
   _ Number of visitors aged 2-11: 392,000.
</P>
<P>
   _ Content: For children, information and games based on Disney
characters and properties; for adults, information about shopping,
visits to Disneyworld and making other Disney vacation travel
plans. The site also offers a $5.95 a month membership in Disney's
Club Blast, which offers ``premium'' kids' content, including free
e-mail.
</P>
<P>
   _ Privacy policy: Collects personal information during contest
or sweepstakes registration, subscription registration and online
shopping or when visitors submit content for online activities like
voting or bulletin boards.
</P>
<P>
   _ Advertising policy: Prohibits ads for hard liquor, tobacco,
firearms, medicines, politics, pornography, and ``sensationalism,''
and restricts many other ads. Ads must be clearly identified. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PBS ONLINE: www.pbs.org
</P>
<P>
   _ Number of unique visitors in February: 1.9 million.
</P>
<P>
   _ Number of visitors aged 2-11: 170,000.
</P>
<P>
   _ Content: Information on public television characters like the
Teletubbies, Barney the Dinosaur and Arthur, educational games, and
links to affiliate sites that focus on specific PBS programs.
</P>
<P>
   _ Privacy policy: No child's personal information is ever posted
online or shared with a third party without a parent's written
consent.
</P>
<P>
   _ Advertising policy: No ads appear on the site. Information
about the sale or availability or program-related or nonprogram
related goods may not be included on the site. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CHILDREN'S TELEVISION WORKSHOP ONLINE: www.ctw.org
</P>
<P>
   _ Number of unique visitors in February: 300,000.
</P>
<P>
   _ Number of visitors aged 2-11: 45,000.
</P>
<P>
   _ Content: Features for pre-schoolers, older kids and parents. A
new Baby Workshop with advice for parents of very young children
will be started in the near future.
</P>
<P>
   _ Privacy policy: No personal information collected from
children younger than 13 without parental consent. Personal
information is collected from parents who want to receive an e-mail
newsletter, who participate in public discussion groups or who
enter sweepstakes. No personal information is shared with third
parties.
</P>
<P>
   _ Advertising policy: No ads appear on pages with content aimed
at pre-schoolers. All ads on the site are clearly identified.
</P>
</TEXT>
