have come about the school shootings in Oregon and Arkansas and
Kentucky. A review of those cases, and two compelling studies that
have received little attention, show striking details between those
and the one's ivolved in Tuesday's incidentg _ all were smart,
troubled kids, into junk culture, had easy access to guns, weren't
taken seriously and were angry at the in crowd. An news analysis.
By Timothy Egan.
</P>
