<HEADLINE>
MOVIE REVIEW: ``NEVER BEEN KISSED'' 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 Includes one color slide of Drew Barrymore (left) and David
Arquette in a scene from the movie ``Never Been Kissed.'' (Credit:
Photo by Suzanne Hanover. Copyright 1999 Twentieth Century Fox.) 
 By PUJA MAEWAL 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``NEVER BEEN KISSED''
</P>
<P>
   Starring: Drew Barrymore, David Arquette, Molly Shannon.
</P>
<P>
   Plot: Josie, a fresh-out-of-college copy editor for the Chicago
Sun Times newspaper, is sent on an assignment: to go back to high
school to find a hot, new story. Fitting in, though, is hard for
Josie, who was a complete geek in her own high school days. (And
the cool crowd is no help to her, either.) But during her second
chance, she discovers a few things about herself and life.
</P>
<P>
   Why go see it?: Drew Barrymore is surprisingly a very convincing
geek, and her character is so lovable that you are rooting for her
till the end. Warning to guys: This is a total chick flick (and a
sweet one, too), so be prepared when your girlfriends drag you to
it, twice. But, to both guys and girls, this original and
refreshing movie will make you laugh out loud through it all.
</P>
<P>
   Reason for rating: PG-13 for mature language and innuendo.
</P>
<P>
   Reviewer's 1 - 10 rating: 7.5.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
