<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KIDS:TV:EARTH-DAY-CLASSACTS-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TV: EARTH MATTERS 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   GOING NATIVE
</P>
<P>
   The Disney Channel folks are getting into the spirit of Earth
Day with a marathon of its animal adventure series, ``Going Wild
With Jeff Corwin.'' Focusing on conservation, preservation and
endangered species, the marathon will take viewers to Costa Rica,
Florida and Washington state to explore rain forests, and unusual
and/or endangered creatures such as manatees and bald eagles.
</P>
<P>
   The marathon will be from 6:00 to 8:00 p.m. on Thursday, April
22, on the Disney Channel.
</P>
<P>
   Jeff Corwin's Top 10 Ways to Celebrate Earth Day:
</P>
<P>
   1. Go natural. Skip hair spray and other aerosol products for
the day.
</P>
<P>
   2. Take a hike. Walk or ride your bike to work or school or
car-pool with others.
</P>
<P>
   3. Donate newspapers, books and magazines to libraries and
schools if you are done reading them.
</P>
<P>
   4. Bring a tote bag to the market instead of using paper or
plastic.
</P>
<P>
   5. Find a cause you believe in and donate your time to a charity
or nonprofit organization that supports that cause.
</P>
<P>
   6. Send a letter to your state senator or U.S. congressman in
support of proposals or laws that protect endangered species or
natural habitats.
</P>
<P>
   7. Only wash clothes that are dirty. Wear something more than
once before washing.
</P>
<P>
   8. Turn off the water while you brush your teeth.
</P>
<P>
   9. Turn off the lights one hour early tonight. Get in the
practice of turning lights off when you leave a room.
</P>
<P>
   10. Use the three R's: Reduce, reuse, recycle.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
