<HEADLINE>
STAR STRUCK? CHECK OUT YOUR WEEK 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By Students SARABETH BALON and NICK FOREMAN 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Before finalizing your activities, take time to read the
following horoscope, which is a fun way to plan your week.
</P>
<P>
   TAURUS (April 20 - May 20): Spring is your prosperous time of
the year. Not only is it when your birthday falls, but it is time
to celebrate life. Well, live it up! Go out and do something
daring. This is your time to throw off the oppression of the rest
of the year.
</P>
<P>
   GEMINI (May 21 - June 20): Start thinking of ways to make money
this summer. If you begin your business ventures now, you will be
ahead of your competition. During the course of the week, play by
the rules. Your parents are keeping a watchful eye on you and will
be quick to make the punishment fit the crime.
</P>
<P>
   CANCER (June 21 - July 22): You will be surprised this week when
you least expect it. The events that will happen during the week
will overwhelm you with happiness. Let your joy shine through you.
When you see someone who appears to be down in the dumps about
something, cheer that person up.
</P>
<P>
   LEO (July 23 - Aug. 22): If you really want something from your
parents, you have to play your cards right. Take the initiative to
do a chore or two around the house. Come home before you have to.
Work really hard to do well on your homework. After all this is
done, then ask away.
</P>
<P>
   VIRGO (Aug. 23 - Sept. 22): Give things a chance. All too often,
you trust your initial instincts. Be wary of doing this, because it
may cause you to miss out on the experience of a lifetime. This
week, make it your challenge to try something you are not too sure
about or to befriend someone you initially would not have.
</P>
<P>
   LIBRA (Sept. 23 - Oct. 22): Do not be surprised if something
great falls at your feet. You have faced a lot of disappointment
lately and are long overdue for something to be handed to you. You
and your hottie will gain a new respect for each other. It is the
little things that make a relationship work, so be open to any
ideas that he or she brings up.
</P>
<P>
   SCORPIO (Oct. 23 - Nov. 21): The word ``bad'' will not even be
in your vocab this week. Nothing but the best will rain on yonot
see how great some of these gifts are until you get some time to
really enjoy what you have received. Hold your head up so you can
see exactly where you are going. You might need to follow this path
later on down the road.
</P>
<P>
   SAGITTARIUS (Nov. 22 - Dec. 21): You mean more to your friends
and family than you can ever imagine. You are the responsible one,
the fun one, and the one everybody trusts. Hardly anyone else can
hold all three of those labels and still have enough sanity to
realize when it is too much. You need to keep yourself healthy,
because your friends feed off you.
</P>
<P>
   CAPRICORN (Dec. 22 - Jan. 19): You might find yourself
regretting a lot of missed chances this week. One big one will be
brought to your attention at school. Your friends have you on a
pedestal. You do not need to justify yourself to your friends for
your decisions, because they are yours. Regret is a feeling that
passes when something bigger and better comes along.
</P>
<P>
   AQUARIUS (Jan. 20 - Feb. 18): You need to get back into the
swing of things, because lately you have been too busy to eat,
sleep or do anything right. This week will be tough, but it will
give you some time to prepare yourself for getting back on the
right track. Live for Friday; all your troubles will seem to fall
away.
</P>
<P>
   PISCES (Feb. 19 - March 20): Expect a subtle twist in the way
that you view people this week. You will find redeeming qualities
in people whom you never had any interest in before. You are
allowing yourself to get past the outward appearance for the first
time in a long while. However, that means that some of your dearest
friends might end up in a different light, but stick with them.
</P>
<P>
   ARIES (March 21 - April 19): Every once in a while, one comes
across a week or two when everything goes right. This week will be
like that for you. When it appears that things are going sour,
something will remedy the situation. Enjoy your good fortune and
allow it to play a key role in your planning.
</P>
<P>
