digits they had to write in to show the losses, $897,000,000 for
the year. The company blamed the loss on ``unusual'' costs such as
lawsuits, Y2K preparedness and payments to fired executives.
(Sedore, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   BIZMAGS _ Sex is bad for business. So says Fortune (May 10) in a
cover story on the variety of problems U.S. corporations are
dealing with from sexual harassment to cybersex on company time to
expense account abuse. (Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
