of big telecommunications takeovers. By Edmund L. Andrews.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic is being sent to NYT graphics clients.
Non-subscribers can make individual purchase by calling (888)
603-1036 or (888) 346-9867.)
</P>
<P>
   (The story is scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Center)
</P>
<P>
   TELECOM (Rome) _ Two of Europe's largest telecommunications
companies, Telecom Italia SpA and Deutsche Telekom AG, have agreed
to merge in a share swap worth almost $95 billion, creating what
would be the world's largest phone company, after the Italian
company obtained assurances that Germany would not interfere in the
combined company's operations. By John Tagliabue.
</P>
