OUT-WALKER (Bridgeport, Calif.) _ Story on the West Walker River
cattle-damage restoration project _ 9 miles of cow-damaged
streambanks along the West Walker River near Sonora Bridge. ``It's
news to see cowboys and fishery biologists working together,'' DFG
fishery biologist Steve Parmenter said. 
By Rob Wheat. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
OUT-CUTTHROAT (Bridgeport, Calif.) _ The history of the Eastern
Sierra is filled with cutthroats. A renegade criminal who shot a
member of a local posse led to the naming of Convict Lake. There
was more than one murder on the streets of Bodie during its
goldrush heyday. And the water barons from Los Angeles were
relentless and ruthless in securing virtually all of the region's
water rights in the region. But north of Conway Summit, there was a
cutthroat that preceded even the earliest man in this region _ the
cutthroat trout. 
By Jim Matthews. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
OUT-BROOD (Independence, Calif.) _ The brood stock from Mount
Whitney State Fish Hatchery all go to Diaz Lake and Haiwee
Reservoir, vastly underutilized and underappreaciated fisheries ...
with mammoth trout. 
By Rob Wheat. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
OUT-BISHOP (Bishop, Calif.) _ Hatchery manager Mike Seefeldt's
promise to stock Bishop-area waters with trout for opener for first
time since the 1970s, with designs on giving local kids _ of all
ages _ the chance to fish a bike ride's away from their home, like
he did when he was growing up. 
By Rob Wheat. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
OUT-NIGHT (Bishop, Calif.) _ Last year's experiment in
night-fishing in Mono County was recinded by emergency regulation,
however, the traditional midnight opener remains in effect for Inyo
county. Consult the DFG's fishing regulations for other specifics.
Also will list cost of as fishing license ($27.55 annual or $10 for
a two-day) and minimum fine for fishing without one ($250). 
Daily News Staff. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 

