<P>
   COLO-SCHOOL-SHOOTING (Littleton, Colo.) _ As parents waited in
agony nearby and police squads searched for explosive booby traps
inside, authorities carefully made their way through Columbine High
School on Wednesday where they found the bodies at least 15 people
killed by gunshots or homemade pipe bombs in a massacre Tuesday.
Among the dead were the two members of the junior class who are
believed to have unleashed the carnage before turning their guns on
themselves. By Sam Verhovek.
</P>
<P>
