companies, Telecom Italia SpA and Deutsche Telekom AG, reached a
formal agreement Wednesday night to merge in a share swap valued at
nearly $82 billion after the Italians obtained assurances that
Germany would not interfere in the new combined company's
operations. By John Tagliabue.
</P>
