of former Sen. Bill Bradley will gain the endorsement of Seattle
Mayor Paul Schell on Thursday morning, and a contingent of about 15
state legislators will show their backing at a dinner on Thursday
night. After months of quiet visits, Bradley will break out his
presidential campaign in a state that has traditionally smiled on
reformist, insurgent Democrats.
