<P>
   (NYT7) WASHINGTON -- April 21, 1999 -- NATO-SUMMIT, 4-21 -- John
Scott works on the flags decorating Mellon Auditorium, in the
Interstate Commerce Building, site of the signing of the agreement
which formed NATO 50 years ago, on Wednesday. Originally planned as
a gala celebration of the alliance's 50th anniversary, the summit
in Washington and the documents that leaders plan to issue here are
being shaped by the allied response to Kosovo and the clouded
outlook for its success, allied officials said on Wednesday. (Paul
Hosefros/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT6) TIRANA, Albania -- April 21, 1999 -- KOSOVO-MILITARY-2,
4-21 -- Newly arriving U.S. Army soldiers enter a building for a
briefing on Wednesday at Rinas airport. Responding to criticism
that NATO has no backup plan to send ground troops into Kosovo in
case air strikes are not enough, allied diplomats signaled that the
option was actively being considered. (James Hill/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) TIRANA, Albania -- April 21, 1999 -- KOSOVO-MILITARY,
4-21 -- A soldier waits to guide U.S. Army Black Hawk helicopters,
the two in the foreground, to their landing pads at Rinas Airport
on Wednesday. Six U.S. Apache helicopter gunships arrived in
Albania on Wednesday, increasing the firepower available to NATO
commanders in the Yugoslav conflict. (James Hill/New York Times
Photo)
