A8233 &Cx1f; tad-z
u f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-NCR-EARNINGS22-COX     04-21 0387
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NCR-EARNINGS22-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    NCR stock drops despite strong earnings
 &HT;    By Angela Townsend
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ NCR Corp. on Wednesday suffered it biggest
one-day stock price drop since going public two years ago even
though the company reported stronger-than-expected first-quarter
earnings.
</P>
<P>
   NCR stock (NYSE: NCR) dropped 8 11/16, or 16.3 percent, to 44 in
heavy trading Wednesday. Analysts said the drop reflected concern
over lighter-than-expected sales of NCR's flagship data warehousing
products.
</P>
<P>
   Net income for the quarter, ended March 31, was $3.3 million, or
3 cents per share, compared with breakeven for the same period in
1998.
</P>
<P>
   Operating income improved $26 million from a loss of $34 million
a year ago. Sales for the quarter climbed 1.8 percent to $1.3
billion.
</P>
<P>
   The results exceeded consensus analyst expectations. First Call
Corp. had estimated per-share earnings of one penny for the
quarter.
</P>
<P>
   During a conference call with analysts, NCR Chief Financial
Officer David Bearman said the company still holds to its objective
of doubling its operating income this year.
</P>
<P>
   But Bearman's and NCR Chairman and Chief Executive Lars Nyberg's
answers to analysts' questions about NCR's data warehousing
business, which experienced what the company described as
``near-term weaknesses,'' failed to mitigate analysts' concerns.
</P>
<P>
   ``Hardware sales were half of what was expected,'' said Steven
Milunovich, an analyst with Merrill Lynch Global Securities. While
data warehousing is roughly only 15 percent of NCR's business, it
is a very visible portion that Milunovich called an ``important
swing factor'' in how NCR's stock performs. The closing price
``adequately reflects the risks and concerns,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   NCR Investor Relations Director Sajid Malhotra said, ``We have
to reinforce the message and internally deliver on what the
expectations are. This is about two things: setting the right
expectations, and second, meeting or beating those expectations. I
think we have to do work on both ends of that. But we feel we have
all the elements in place.''
</P>
<P>
   Despite Wednesday big drop, NCR's stock is still ahead about 4
points since the start of the year, Malhotra said.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
